cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper discusses the use of point clouds as a representation of everyday scenes, which is a common topic in computer vision. The paper also proposes a new method for processing point clouds with machine learning algorithms, which is relevant to the sub-category of computer vision.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new method for processing point clouds with machine learning algorithms, which is directly related to the sub-category of machine learning.
3. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper discusses the use of 3D scanning technology and high-resolution meshes, which are relevant to the sub-category of graphics.
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper discusses the use of point clouds for registering high-resolution meshes to noisy 3D scans, which is relevant to the sub-category of robotics.
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new method for processing point clouds with machine learning algorithms, which is relevant to the sub-category of artificial intelligence.
